# Logout Test

# NOTE: Update @jwt_token with a valid token from login
@jwt_token = token

### Step 1: Login first to get a fresh token
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.perez@email.com",
  "password": "mySecurePassword123"
}

###

### Step 2: Test protected route (should work)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/test/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 3: Logout (blacklist the token)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 4: Try protected route again (should fail with "Token has been revoked")
GET http://localhost:3000/api/test/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

